---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const ecosystemDiagram = `<pre><code class="language-mermaid">graph TB
    subgraph Interfaces
        USERS[Lawyers and teams]
        AGENTS[LLMs and agents]
    end

    subgraph "Juca"
        JUCA[Frontend hub&lt;br/&gt;briefing, canvas, reading]
    end

    subgraph "Valter"
        API[REST API]
        MCP[MCP]
        ORCH[Service layer&lt;br/&gt;routing and orchestration]
        INGEST[Grounding adapters&lt;br/&gt;ingestion and handoff]
        RETRIEVAL[Graph-led retrieval]
        REASONING[Verification + reasoning]
    end

    subgraph "Internal providers"
        LECI[Leci&lt;br/&gt;document-first legislation&lt;br/&gt;own runtime and storage]
        DOUTO[Douto&lt;br/&gt;doctrinal artifacts&lt;br/&gt;local pipeline and corpus]
    end

    subgraph "Valter-owned stores"
        PG[(PostgreSQL)]
        QD[(Qdrant)]
        N4J[(Neo4j)]
        RD[(Redis)]
    end

    USERS --&gt; JUCA
    AGENTS --&gt; MCP
    JUCA --&gt; API
    API --&gt; ORCH
    MCP --&gt; ORCH
    ORCH --&gt; INGEST
    ORCH --&gt; RETRIEVAL
    ORCH --&gt; REASONING
    LECI --&gt; INGEST
    DOUTO --&gt; INGEST
    INGEST --&gt; PG
    INGEST --&gt; QD
    INGEST --&gt; N4J
    RETRIEVAL --&gt; PG &amp; QD &amp; N4J &amp; RD
    REASONING --&gt; PG &amp; N4J</code></pre>`;

const searchDiagram = `<pre><code class="language-mermaid">flowchart LR
    Q[Legal question] --&gt; ENTRY[Entry into Valter]
    ENTRY --&gt; GRAPH[Neo4j traversal + graph retrieval&lt;br/&gt;primary path]
    ENTRY --&gt; SEARCH[Parallel lexical and semantic search&lt;br/&gt;support and fallback]
    GRAPH --&gt; FUSE[Fusion and calibration]
    SEARCH --&gt; FUSE
    FUSE --&gt; GROUND[Grounding and verification&lt;br/&gt;Leci and Douto when needed]
    GROUND --&gt; EXPLAIN[Traceable reasoning chain]
    EXPLAIN --&gt; RESULT[REST or MCP response]</code></pre>`;
---

<DocsLayout title="Architecture" description="System architecture and data flow diagrams.">
  <h1>Architecture</h1>

  <p>
    sens.legal is an ecosystem of <strong>four projects</strong>. Juca is the
    frontend hub; Valter is the central jurisprudence and reasoning backend; Leci
    handles document-first legislative grounding; and Douto supplies internal
    doctrinal artifacts. The diagrams below summarize that split.
  </p>

  <h2>Ecosystem Overview</h2>

  <p>
    The frontend and LLM agents enter through different surfaces, but the canonical
    backend remains Valter. Leci and Douto feed that backend with specialized
    grounding rather than competing to be the frontend or the central legal backend.
  </p>

  <p>
    The diagram below is a <strong>boundary and ownership view</strong>. The data
    stores on the right belong to Valter, while Leci and Douto remain upstream
    providers with their own runtimes and data pipelines. They contribute through
    ingestion and grounding contracts instead of coupling directly to Valter's
    internal storage layer.
  </p>

  <p>
    REST and MCP are <strong>parallel entry surfaces</strong> into the same Valter
    service layer. They differ in client protocol, not in system ownership: both
    can reach the same orchestration, retrieval, verification, and reasoning
    capabilities underneath.
  </p>

  <Fragment set:html={ecosystemDiagram} />

  <h2>Search Pipeline</h2>

  <p>
    Valter now follows a <strong>graph-led</strong> architecture: the legal graph
    becomes the primary discovery path, while lexical and semantic search run in
    parallel to expand coverage and provide graceful degradation. The final answer
    may include verification, additional grounding, and a reasoning chain.
  </p>

  <Fragment set:html={searchDiagram} />

  <h2>Project roles</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Project</th><th>Role</th><th>Main integration</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>Valter</code></td><td>Search, verification, reasoning, canonical APIs, multi-tribunal knowledge graph (2.2M decisions), 3-stage LLM chat pipeline, and OAuth 2.0 auth. Neo4j for Startups partner.</td><td>REST API (50+ endpoints) + MCP (31 tools)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Juca</code></td><td>User experience, briefing, and canvas</td><td>Consumes Valter and, later, Leci</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Leci</code></td><td>Document-first legislation and reliable grounding</td><td>Supplies statutes and provisions to consumers</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Douto</code></td><td>Local doctrine pipeline and internal artifacts</td><td>Controlled handoff into Valter</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Valter-owned data layer</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>PostgreSQL</strong> for documents, metadata, and operational state</li>
    <li><strong>Qdrant</strong> for semantic vector search</li>
    <li><strong>Neo4j Aura</strong> for graph-led retrieval, explanation, and legal relationships (Neo4j for Startups program)</li>
    <li><strong>Redis</strong> for cache and operational controls</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <a href="https://valter.sens.legal/architecture/diagrams/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      View the canonical architecture docs on Valter &rarr;
    </a>
  </p>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  th, td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  th {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
</style>

<script>
  // @ts-ignore — CDN module, no type declarations
  import mermaid from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@11/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs';
  mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: false, theme: 'default' });

  document.querySelectorAll('pre:has(code.language-mermaid)').forEach((pre) => {
    const code = pre.querySelector('code');
    if (!code) return;
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'mermaid';
    div.textContent = code.textContent;
    pre.replaceWith(div);
  });

  mermaid.run();
</script>
